<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="425" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="425">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="425">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson &amp; Armitage &amp; Harris" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Leucotrichia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leucotrichia ruiteri" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="425" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruiteri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">Leucotrichia ruiteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. is most similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. hispida" pageId="0" pageNumber="425" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">L. hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as both species bear prominent setae on the posteroventral production of sternum VIII, a bilobed phallus apex, and a similar shaped inferior appendage. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson &amp; Armitage &amp; Harris" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Leucotrichia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leucotrichia ruiteri" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="425" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruiteri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">Leucotrichia ruiteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated by the single, elongate seta on sternum VIII compared to the cluster of setae present on 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. hispida" pageId="0" pageNumber="425" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">L. hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Additionally, the forewings of 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. ruiteri" pageId="0" pageNumber="425" rank="species" species="ruiteri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">L. ruiteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are modified with a large setae-filled pocket, while those of 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. hispida" pageId="0" pageNumber="425" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">L. hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are unmodified.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="425" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="425">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="425">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">Male.</emphasis>
Length of forewing 2.0-2.1 mm (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">n</emphasis>
= 4). Forewing with large pocket filled with scales (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Modifications A Forewing, Leucotrichia ruiteri sp. nov. B head and scape, Leucotrichia chiriquiensis Flint, 1970 C head and antennae, Leucotrichia fairchildi Flint, 1970. Fig. 2 B and 2 C modified from Thomson and Holzenthal (2015)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77371.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713490" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">2A</figureCitation>
); hindwing unmodified. Head unmodified, with three ocelli; antennae unmodified. Tibial spur count 1, 3, 4. Color in alcohol brown. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">Genitalia</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Abdominal sternum VII slender, elongate (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Leucotrichia ruiteri sp. nov. Male genitalia: A segments VII-VIII and segment IX margin, lateral B segments IX-X, lateral (base of phallus crosshatched) C segments IX-X, dorsal D segments VII-IX, ventral E phallus, lateral F phallus, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77371.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713502" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">14A, D</figureCitation>
). Sternum VIII with posteroventral production bearing prominent apical seta (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Leucotrichia ruiteri sp. nov. Male genitalia: A segments VII-VIII and segment IX margin, lateral B segments IX-X, lateral (base of phallus crosshatched) C segments IX-X, dorsal D segments VII-IX, ventral E phallus, lateral F phallus, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77371.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713502" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">14A</figureCitation>
); in ventral view posterior margin concave (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Leucotrichia ruiteri sp. nov. Male genitalia: A segments VII-VIII and segment IX margin, lateral B segments IX-X, lateral (base of phallus crosshatched) C segments IX-X, dorsal D segments VII-IX, ventral E phallus, lateral F phallus, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77371.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713502" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">14D</figureCitation>
). Segment IX anterolateral margin convex, posterolateral margin straight with slight irregularity (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Leucotrichia ruiteri sp. nov. Male genitalia: A segments VII-VIII and segment IX margin, lateral B segments IX-X, lateral (base of phallus crosshatched) C segments IX-X, dorsal D segments VII-IX, ventral E phallus, lateral F phallus, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77371.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713502" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">14B</figureCitation>
); dorsally, anterior margin concave, posterior margin broadly convex (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Leucotrichia ruiteri sp. nov. Male genitalia: A segments VII-VIII and segment IX margin, lateral B segments IX-X, lateral (base of phallus crosshatched) C segments IX-X, dorsal D segments VII-IX, ventral E phallus, lateral F phallus, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77371.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713502" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">14C</figureCitation>
). Tergum X with dorsal sclerite with irregular dorsal margin; ventral sclerite semi-elliptic with knoblike projection mesally on posterior margin; membranous apex subquadrate (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Leucotrichia ruiteri sp. nov. Male genitalia: A segments VII-VIII and segment IX margin, lateral B segments IX-X, lateral (base of phallus crosshatched) C segments IX-X, dorsal D segments VII-IX, ventral E phallus, lateral F phallus, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77371.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713502" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">14B, C</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate with dorsal arm simple, with slight preapical emargination on dorsal margin, apex truncate (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Leucotrichia ruiteri sp. nov. Male genitalia: A segments VII-VIII and segment IX margin, lateral B segments IX-X, lateral (base of phallus crosshatched) C segments IX-X, dorsal D segments VII-IX, ventral E phallus, lateral F phallus, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77371.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713502" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">14B</figureCitation>
); ventral arm narrowing apically, ventral margin slightly sinuate, in ventral view subovate with narrow basal projection and small rounded apical emargination (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Leucotrichia ruiteri sp. nov. Male genitalia: A segments VII-VIII and segment IX margin, lateral B segments IX-X, lateral (base of phallus crosshatched) C segments IX-X, dorsal D segments VII-IX, ventral E phallus, lateral F phallus, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77371.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713502" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">14B, D</figureCitation>
). Inferior appendage broadest mesally, with small dorsal subapical peg-like seta, apex rounded (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Leucotrichia ruiteri sp. nov. Male genitalia: A segments VII-VIII and segment IX margin, lateral B segments IX-X, lateral (base of phallus crosshatched) C segments IX-X, dorsal D segments VII-IX, ventral E phallus, lateral F phallus, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77371.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713502" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">14B</figureCitation>
); ventrally slender, with digitate basal projections, apex slightly hooked on inner margin (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Leucotrichia ruiteri sp. nov. Male genitalia: A segments VII-VIII and segment IX margin, lateral B segments IX-X, lateral (base of phallus crosshatched) C segments IX-X, dorsal D segments VII-IX, ventral E phallus, lateral F phallus, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77371.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713502" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">14D</figureCitation>
). Phallus tubular basally, constricted at midlength with typical median complex bearing basal loop and pair of spherical 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“windows”">&quot;windows&quot;</normalizedToken>
; apex membranous with internal sclerotized structures and two apical lobes extending dorsad (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Leucotrichia ruiteri sp. nov. Male genitalia: A segments VII-VIII and segment IX margin, lateral B segments IX-X, lateral (base of phallus crosshatched) C segments IX-X, dorsal D segments VII-IX, ventral E phallus, lateral F phallus, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77371.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713502" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">14E, F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77371.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713502" pageId="0" pageNumber="425" start="Figure 14" startId="F14">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="425">
